        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> At 22, I still leave taunt on.  I am kill dwarves on sister island and I leach dorf, run to pet, tap tap tap until I'm almost dead, back up, tap twice, move back in.  Inefficient as hell manawise, but I end fight full health, pet health depends on how much channeling through I do.</P><P>This accomplishes several things.  Main reason I do it this way is because I want my defence up as high as possible, and this gets it up there.  Also do it because I can take the two dwarves that are close to eachother as they spawn.  The male is lvl 25 (red) and the female is lvl 24 (yellow) and both give about a full blue, just a tad bit under.</P><P>But in this case I leave taunt on to keep the mob hitting my pet when I back up... every now and then I out agro the pet, but usually another good taunt will get em off me... if not, FD get up and tap again.  </P><P>Later, if you want to agro kite the mob (piss him off and run from him until you are far enough away to cast again) you want pet taunt off.</P><P>Lastly, taunt doesn't take a pet attack away.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
