        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=14514&TOPIC_ID=1458&FORUM_ID=8&CAT_ID=2&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=To+Taunt+or+not+to+Taunt&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Leave pet taunt on till higher levels. Having the pet taunting when fear kiting can save yer ass muchly at lower levels. The number of times Jabober saved me by keeping a mobs attention while I ran my ass of to the zone, I dont even like to think about.</P><P>Pet taunting really only becomes an issue in groups/raids on higher level mobs, where careful aggro management becomes a major issue.</P><P>56 DE Necromancer<BR><br><BR><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=49001" target="_blank">Profile</a><BR><a href="http://sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/" target="_blank">Ulaa's web site</a><br><BR><img src="http://www.sizzlesites.com/Ulaa/sig.jpg" border=0><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
      </tr>

