			&nbsp;<a href="JavaScript:openWindow('pop_mail.asp?id=1821')"><img src="icon_email.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Email Poster" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&REPLY_ID=15611&TOPIC_ID=1458&FORUM_ID=8&CAT_ID=2&Forum_Title=Newbie+Hall&Topic_Title=To+Taunt+or+not+to+Taunt&M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height=15 width=15 alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2"> Very rarely, if ever, will your pet taunt a mob off of another player in a group.  I don't know if mine ever has and I always leave taunt on in a group.</P><P>Now, when aggro kiting things are different.  This is the only time I ever turn off my pet's taunt.  If you want to aggro kite (have a mob chase you around with your pet beating on it's back) then you don't want to have your pet taunt it off of you.  It suck to throw a couple of dots on something, start running thinking it's chasing you only to find out that your pet has taunted it off of you and you're half way across the zone already.</P><P>So IMO leave taunt on at all times except for when aggro kiting.</P><P><P><br><img src="http://www.imahosting.com/sigs/cortosig.jpg" border=0><br>40th Gnecromancer<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height=15 width=15 border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
